messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I'm out here right now, and I locked my keys in my car.
Is there any way that someone can come out here and unlock my car?
Commercial services are available in town to do that. Police and fire cannot assist with that.
What do you mean by commercial services?
I mean you'll have to pay to have it done.
Okay, what's the closest service?
The closest is Massings. Their number is 987.
Alright, thank you.
Good day.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
It's not an emergency. The only way I know how to get in touch with this woman is through Officer Bourbon County.
Okay, I need you to call back on a non-emergency line.
How do I do that? What's the number?
Thank you.
911, what's your emergency?
There's some raccoons in my attic, and it sounds like they've made their way into the attic somehow from outside.
It sounds like they're trying to scratch their way into the house.
You dialed 911 for raccoons in your attic?
Yeah, because animal control came out one other time and said they could go up there and get the raccoons.
The animal control people came out last year when a snake got in the house.
I haven't called my landlord yet. Should I call her first?
What's your name and phone number?
Teresa. My number is 749.
You definitely need to call your landlord. Next time, call on the administrative line. This is taking up an emergency line.
I'm sorry, what's the administrative line?
2100? Okay, I'll call that line. Thank you.
We'll get a hold of animal control. Uh-huh. All right, thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
9-1-1, what's your emergency? I hear you breathing.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I'm sorry, but the fireworks are still going on.
I'm sorry, you cannot call 911 for that.
Thank you.
You're welcome.
